race.description: Comfort Inn Bay Of Isles Handicap (C2)
race.comment: PETITE VITESSE (2) was solid enough at Northam first-up without a trial and should be fitter for that effort. She'll find this an easier assignment today and she is a second-up winner in the past. Likely to get back from the draw but can mow her rivals down with improvement anticipated. RULING DAME (9) drops back to 1300m today following a sound effort at Albany just last week. She'll need some luck from the wide draw, but she remains down in the weights after Mahony's claim. Rates well on her past couple of efforts and can be in the finish. WIFE SAYS YES (10) was just fair at Belmont first-up from a break but looks an improver coming into this suitable assignment. She hasn't won for a while, but she's turned in some solid ratings which would see her competitive in this field. Include. MORIAH (13) can be in the finish as she comes here on the fresh side. VENTURO (1) is next best.
